        "text": "*[Bug 19021] history function does not work correctly*\n<https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=19021>\n\nSebastian Meyer (<mailto:seb.meyer@fau.de|seb.meyer@fau.de>) changed:\n\n           What    |Removed                     |Added\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n                 CC|                            |seb.meyer@fau.de\n\n--- Comment #1 from Sebastian Meyer (<mailto:seb.meyer@fau.de|seb.meyer@fau.de>) ---\nBoth plain-text help and history() eventually use file.show(). If you want\noutput to appear directly in the console on Windows, set\n\n    options(pager = \"console\")\n\nThis should solve your original problem.\n\nNote that `Rterm.exe --ess` disables getline, which causes `history()` to fail\nas described (reproduced in R 4.1.3 and R 4.5.1) from the `readLines(file1)`\nstep:\n\n```\n&gt; history()\nError in file(con, \"r\") : cannot open the connection\nIn addition: Warning message:\nIn file(con, \"r\") :\n  cannot open file 'C:\\rtools45\\tmp\\RtmpusNVEA\\Rrawhistc3458034fcb': No such\nfile or directory\n```\n\nOr also:\n\n```\n&gt; savehistory(\"Rhist\")\n&gt; file.exists(\"Rhist\")\n[1] FALSE\n```\n\nThis is expected given the 'Details' of `help(\"history\")`. Similarly, the\nreported error on FreeBSD can be reproduced by starting R with command-line\noption `--no-readline` on Linux, so `capabilities(\"cledit\")` is false. Citing\nfrom `?history`:\n\n     Windows:\n          The functions described here work in 'Rgui' and interactive\n          'Rterm' but not in batch use of 'Rterm' nor in embedded\/DCOM\n          versions.\n\n     Unix-alikes:\n          The functions described here work under the 'readline'\n          command-line interface but may not otherwise (for example, in\n          batch use or in an embedded application).  Note that R can be\n          built without 'readline'.\n\nSo I am inclined to close this bug report as invalid.",
