        "subtype": "bot_message",
        "text": "*[Bug 19021] history function does not work correctly*\n<https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=19021>\n\nPeter Dalgaard (<mailto:pd.mes@cbs.dk|pd.mes@cbs.dk>) changed:\n\n           What    |Removed                     |Added\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n                 CC|                            |pd.mes@cbs.dk\n\n--- Comment #2 from Peter Dalgaard (<mailto:pd.mes@cbs.dk|pd.mes@cbs.dk>) ---\nAlternatively move to wishlist. \n\nIt would seem that the reporter has been confused by history() being coupled to\nthe command line editing facilities and thus depending on their availability.\n\nArguably, the history mechanism could be made independent of the user\ninterface: E.g., store lines executed in a circular buffer and have history()\nwork on that and display via the pager.",
        "username": "r-bugs notifier",
        "icons": {
            "emoji": ":robot_face:"
        },
        "type": "message",
        "ts": "1773787701.975069",
        "bot_id": "B06769YJX9Q",
